		<ol>
				<li>Regular members Individuals who joined in support of the purpose of this corporation.</li>
				<li>Adult members Individuals who have joined in support of the purpose of this corporation.</li>
				<li>Child members Individuals who have joined in support of the purpose of this corporation.</li>
				<li>Kids member Individuals who joined in support of the purpose of this corporation.</li>
				<li>Family members Parents and their families who joined in support of the purpose of this corporation.</li>
				<li>Sponsor members Individuals and groups who have joined to support the purpose of this corporation and to support the business.</li>
				<li>Gold Sponsor Member Individuals and groups who have joined to support the purpose of this corporation and to support the business.</li>
				<li>Silver sponsor members Individuals and groups who have joined to support the purpose of this corporation and to support the business.</li>
				<li>Bronze sponsor members Individuals and groups who have joined to support the purpose of this corporation and to support the business.</li>
				<li>Supporting group members Individuals and groups who have joined to support the purpose of this corporation and support the business.</li>
		</ol>

		<h3>Article 3 (Enrollment)</h3>

		<ol>
				<li>Regarding the enrolment of members, the conditions of the NAMTBA Code of Conduct will be accepted. By following the guidelines of the NAMTBA Code of Conduct, we will continue to keep trails safe, protect nature and support the maintenance of mountain biking culture. Respect the environment.</li>
				<li>Those who are going to join as a memberRepresentative Director and Deputy Representative Directors, according to the membership application form specified separately by Representative Director and Deputy Representative Director shall apply to the Representative Director and Deputy Representative Director. They must admit membership unless there is a good reason not to expect membership.</li>
				<li>If the representative director does not approve the membership of the item set forth in the preceding paragraph, he / she must promptly notify the person in writing with the reason.</li>
				<li>The annual membership fee will be paid by the prescribed method within 14 days including the application date, and the membership will be established on the day when the secretariat confirms the payment of the annual membership fee.</li>
		</ol>

		<h3>Article 4 (annual membership fee)</h3>
		<p>The annual membership fee is set as follows.</p>
		<ol>
				<li>Free admission fee for regular members, Annual membership fee 1,000 yen.</li>
				<li>Free admission fee for adult members, Annual membership fee 5,000 yen.</li>
				<li>Free admission fee for child members, Annual membership fee 2,500 yen.</li>
				<li>Kids member admission fee is free, No annual membership fee.</li>
				<li>Free admission fee for family members, Annual membership fee 9,000 yen (Per family living together up to six family members).</li>
				<li>Free admission fee for supporting group members, Annual membership fee 50,000 yen per unit 1 or more.</li>
				<li>Free admission fee for sponsor members, Annual membership fee 50,000 yen.</li>
				<li>Gold sponsor member No admission fee, Annual membership fee 500,000 yen per unit 1 to 10 units.</li>
				<li>Silver sponsor member No admission fee, Annual membership fee 250,000 yen per unit 1 or more.</li>
				<li>Bronze Sponsor Member Admission Free, Annual membership fee 50,000 yen per unit 1 or more.</li>
				<li>It will be delivered by the prescribed method every October.</li>
		</ol>

		<h3>Article 5 (Membership and validity period)</h3>
		<ol>
				<li>Regular member,Adult member,Child members, Kid members, Family members, Sponsor members, Gold sponsor members, Silver sponsor members, Bronze sponsor members, `Supporting group members, the validity period of the membership qualification is until the last day of the settlement of accounts of the corporation (October 31st every year).</li>
				<li>The validity period specified in the preceding paragraph shall be extended for one year from the day after the expiration unless requested by the member or the corporation, and the same shall apply thereafter.</li>
				<li>If a member who joins as an individual withdraws or dies, the membership of the member shall be lost and the qualification cannot be passed on to a third party.</li>
				<li>If a member who joins a group inherits the member's qualification due to a merger, etc., the group member who inherits the qualification must promptly notify the corporation in writing or by electronic means.</li>
				<li>Membership cannot be transferred, lent, sold, etc.</li>
		</ol>

