		<p>The general meeting is composed of Regular members (Board Members) as stipulated in the articles of incorporation of this corporation, and supporting members and general members do not have voting rights.</p>

		<h3>Article 7 (Change of member information)</h3>
		<ol>
				<li>When there is a change in the contents registered by the membership application, the member must promptly notify the corporation in writing or by electronic means.</li>
				<li>The corporation shall not be liable for any disadvantages/damages/losses suffered by the members without the notification set forth in the preceding paragraph.</li>
		</ol>

		<h3>Article 8 (Disclosure of member information, etc.)</h3>
		<ol>
				<li>NAMTBA Officer Administrator can share information such as the address, phone number, and email of the company where the regular member works and the member. However, a Regular member without the permission of this corporation will not do so for any reason.</li>
				<li>In principle, our corporation will not disclose member information to the outside.</li>
				<li>If it is determined that the member's remarks, etc. will be disadvantageous to a third party, the member's private information may be notified to the police or related organizations. In addition, when a court, public prosecutor's office, police, bar association, or an organization with similar authority requests disclosure of member's private information and access log information based on the provisions of laws and regulations, information will be provided as necessary. We may disclose it.</li>
				<li>The member shall not object to this as long as the above measures of the corporation are taken in accordance with the law, and the corporation shall not be liable.</li>
